WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:17.395 align:middle line:90%


00:00:17.395 --> 00:00:21.868 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:21.868 --> 00:01:03.119 align:middle line:90%


00:01:03.119 --> 00:01:06.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Traces of civilizations
that were born, grew,

00:01:06.230 --> 00:01:09.200 align:middle line:84%
and then disappeared over the
centuries can be found in most

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:10.890 align:middle line:90%
countries around the world.

00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.560 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they perished
from unknown causes.

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:15.890 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they were destroyed
by the violent onslaughts

00:01:15.890 --> 00:01:17.420 align:middle line:90%
of new conquerors.

00:01:17.420 --> 00:01:21.470 align:middle line:84%
The ruins we admire today
emerge from the mists of time.

00:01:21.470 --> 00:01:24.200 align:middle line:84%
Many of them are perfectly
aligned astronomically,

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:27.080 align:middle line:84%
with huge stones molded
into elaborate forms that

00:01:27.080 --> 00:01:30.740 align:middle line:84%
are truly astonishing
feats of engineering.

00:01:30.740 --> 00:01:33.560 align:middle line:84%
Structures so massive and
sophisticated that they

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.230 align:middle line:84%
would be a challenge even
to modern technology.

00:01:36.230 --> 00:01:38.690 align:middle line:10%
Some of the most fascinating
archaeological sites

00:01:38.690 --> 00:01:40.340 align:middle line:10%
in the world are in Peru.

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:42.800 align:middle line:84%
These have been carefully
studied for many years,

00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:44.720 align:middle line:84%
leading to the discovery
of traces which

00:01:44.720 --> 00:01:48.020 align:middle line:84%
range from faint to surprising,
impossible to interpret

00:01:48.020 --> 00:01:50.420 align:middle line:84%
with the tools and knowledge
we currently possess.

00:01:50.420 --> 00:01:53.060 align:middle line:84%
Traces can be found in the
ancient remains in archaic

00:01:53.060 --> 00:01:55.910 align:middle line:84%
myths, in the oral traditions
handed down from the lost

00:01:55.910 --> 00:01:59.270 align:middle line:84%
people, even in the chronicles
of the conquistadores,

00:01:59.270 --> 00:02:02.570 align:middle line:84%
gods who mingled with men and
built fantastic cities bound

00:02:02.570 --> 00:02:05.720 align:middle line:84%
by massive walls, mysterious
tunnels that are believed

00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:08.180 align:middle line:84%
to have once linked
these ancient sites,

00:02:08.180 --> 00:02:10.281 align:middle line:84%
bearers of knowledge
and civilization,

00:02:10.281 --> 00:02:12.530 align:middle line:84%
divinities who travelled the
four corners of the Earth

00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:13.850 align:middle line:90%
and knew how to fly.

00:02:13.850 --> 00:02:16.640 align:middle line:84%
There is a strange similarity
between the ruins and myths

00:02:16.640 --> 00:02:18.260 align:middle line:84%
found in many
parts of the world,

00:02:18.260 --> 00:02:21.440 align:middle line:84%
almost an echo of a long-lost
forgotten civilization,

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:24.470 align:middle line:84%
a highly developed breed of
superior beings who disappeared

00:02:24.470 --> 00:02:28.400 align:middle line:84%
thousands of years ago, a mother
culture we have no memory of.

00:02:28.400 --> 00:02:30.940 align:middle line:90%


00:02:30.940 --> 00:02:34.090 align:middle line:84%
Attracted by the mystery and
magnetic pull of these places,

00:02:34.090 --> 00:02:39.635 align:middle line:84%
we set off to explore them and
capture their essence on film.

00:02:39.635 --> 00:02:44.108 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

