00:07:37.990 --> 00:07:41.540 align:middle line:90%
Cusco means navel of the world.

00:07:41.540 --> 00:07:44.000 align:middle line:84%
Here, you can still see
the remains of ancient Inca

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.730 align:middle line:84%
buildings and temples that
the Spanish incorporated

00:07:46.730 --> 00:07:49.390 align:middle line:90%
into their own buildings.

00:07:49.390 --> 00:07:51.340 align:middle line:84%
Some of them are
particularly interesting

00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:53.050 align:middle line:84%
from a construction
point-of-view,

00:07:53.050 --> 00:07:55.270 align:middle line:84%
so surprisingly
sophisticated that they

00:07:55.270 --> 00:07:58.330 align:middle line:84%
would represent a challenge
even to modern builders.

00:07:58.330 --> 00:08:00.880 align:middle line:84%
This dry stone wall
is really astonishing.

00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:02.680 align:middle line:84%
Huge blocks of stone
weighing hundreds

00:08:02.680 --> 00:08:04.990 align:middle line:84%
of pounds in solid
granite, delicately

00:08:04.990 --> 00:08:06.700 align:middle line:84%
chiseled and fitted
one on top of

00:08:06.700 --> 00:08:10.000 align:middle line:84%
the other without any mortar,
apparently haphazardly,

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:14.020 align:middle line:84%
shaped as if they'd been
made of soft plastic clay.

00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:17.240 align:middle line:84%
How were these massive stones
transported and set in place?

00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:19.820 align:middle line:90%


00:08:19.820 --> 00:08:22.100 align:middle line:84%
How could the people of
this ancient civilization

00:08:22.100 --> 00:08:24.680 align:middle line:84%
fit them together so
perfectly without the help

00:08:24.680 --> 00:08:27.450 align:middle line:90%
of modern technology?

00:08:27.450 --> 00:08:30.680 align:middle line:84%
The Incas hadn't
discovered the wheel,

00:08:30.680 --> 00:08:32.429 align:middle line:84%
but their building
techniques bear witness

00:08:32.429 --> 00:08:36.400 align:middle line:84%
to an amazing knowledge of
engineering and architecture.

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:39.120 align:middle line:84%
