blade between them,

00:08:42.570 --> 00:08:45.540 align:middle line:90%
but no mortar has been used.

00:08:45.540 --> 00:08:47.820 align:middle line:84%
It weighs hundreds
of pounds, but it

00:08:47.820 --> 00:08:49.590 align:middle line:90%
isn't one of the largest.

00:08:49.590 --> 00:08:51.150 align:middle line:84%
On the other side
of the building,

00:08:51.150 --> 00:08:52.860 align:middle line:84%
the stones form a
pattern representing

00:08:52.860 --> 00:08:55.410 align:middle line:90%
the outline of a puma.

00:08:55.410 --> 00:08:57.736 align:middle line:90%
Amazingly clever craftsmanship.

00:08:57.736 --> 00:09:04.690 align:middle line:90%


00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:07.080 align:middle line:84%
There's a stone with
14 corners on the wall

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:08.460 align:middle line:90%
of a nearby building.

00:09:08.460 --> 00:09:10.830 align:middle line:84%
It's smaller than the
other, but the craftsmanship

00:09:10.830 --> 00:09:14.996 align:middle line:84%
and its polygonal shaping
is still wonderful.

00:09:14.996 --> 00:09:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And there are still
plenty of surprises

00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.748 align:middle line:90%
to see in the Inca capital.

00:09:18.748 --> 00:09:23.050 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:23.050 --> 00:09:26.880 align:middle line:90%


00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:29.250 align:middle line:84%
A promontory rising on
the outskirts of the city

00:09:29.250 --> 00:09:31.820 align:middle line:90%
dominates Cusco.

00:09:31.820 --> 00:09:34.680 align:middle line:84%
