You can see that
an attempt has been

00:13:16.490 --> 00:13:19.530 align:middle line:84%
made to copy the polygonal
pattern we admired before.

00:13:19.530 --> 00:13:21.350 align:middle line:84%
But even if the blocks
are much smaller,

00:13:21.350 --> 00:13:23.510 align:middle line:84%
the workmanship is
rougher, and the stones

00:13:23.510 --> 00:13:25.820 align:middle line:90%
don't fit together as well.

00:13:25.820 --> 00:13:29.470 align:middle line:90%
Our doubts increase.

00:13:29.470 --> 00:13:31.400 align:middle line:10%
Did the Incas really
build the walls

00:13:31.400 --> 00:13:36.500 align:middle line:10%
we saw in Cusco and the huge
structures at Sacsayhuaman?

00:13:36.500 --> 00:13:41.390 align:middle line:84%
The discrepancy between the
sites makes it seem doubtful.

00:13:41.390 --> 00:13:43.820 align:middle line:84%
We walk over the whole
complex, but the workmanship

00:13:43.820 --> 00:13:46.190 align:middle line:84%
on the walls is the
same everywhere.

00:13:46.190 --> 00:13:48.870 align:middle line:84%
And we begin to
really wonder, who

00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:52.390 align:middle line:84%
built the huge constructions
at Cusco and Sacsayhuaman?

00:13:52.390 --> 00:13:57.130 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:57.130 --> 00:13:59.510 align:middle line:90%


00:13:59.510 --> 00:14:02.480 align:middle line:84%
Here get a helping hand
from Inca tradition.

00:14:02.480 --> 00:14:04.760 align:middle line:84%
Legend says that these
incredible constructions were

00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:07.070 align:middle line:90%
already old when they arrived.

00:14:07.070 --> 00:14:08.810 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
the Incas settled

00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:13.530 align:middle line:84%
on preexisting sites, which
they restored and enlarged.

00:14:13.530 --> 00:14:16.870 align:middle line:84%
Inca tradition also tells us
about the original builder.

00:14:16.870 --> 00:14:20.260 align:middle line:84%
In ancient days after a
terrible cataclysm, which

00:14:20.260 --> 00:14:22.560 align:middle line:84%
had reduced men to
the levels of beasts,

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:26.170 align:middle line:84%
a being came from the south
with superhuman powers.

00:14:26.170 --> 00:14:29.080 align:middle line:84%
He founded a new civilization,
teaching the sciences,

00:14:29.080 --> 00:14:30.880 align:middle line:90%
agriculture, and the arts.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:33.280 align:middle line:84%
He taught men to live
in harmony, animated

00:14:33.280 --> 00:14:37.690 align:middle line:84%
by a spirit of altruism, a being
accompanied by followers called

00:14:37.690 --> 00:14:40.720 align:middle line:84%
the faithful and the
shining, a being who

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:42.700 align:middle line:90%
had incredible skills.

00:14:42.700 --> 00:14:46.660 align:middle line:84%
He could move in the
sky and float on water.

00:14:46.660 --> 00:14:49.570 align:middle line:84%
One of his symbols is
lightning, and his name

00:14:49.570 --> 00:14:52.030 align:middle line:90%
means god of storms.

00:14:52.030 --> 00:14:54.010 align:middle line:90%
He had white skin and a beard.

00:14:54.010 --> 00:14:56.920 align:middle line:90%
His name was Viracocha.

00:14:56.920 --> 00:15:00.080 align:middle line:84%
A divinity who could move in
the sky thousands of years ago,

00:15:00.080 --> 00:15:01.880 align:middle line:90%
who could fly?

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:04.220 align:middle line:84%
A divinity, or the
survivor of an ancient,

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:06.230 align:middle line:84%
highly developed
civilization with

00:15:06.230 --> 00:15:09.770 align:middle line:84%
sophisticated scientific
and technological knowledge.

00:15:09.770 --> 00:15:11.540 align:middle line:90%
This is what the legend implies.

00:15:11.540 --> 00:15:15.620 align:middle line:84%
And Sacsayhuaman has
other surprises for us.

00:15:15.620 --> 00:15:18.307 align:middle line:84%
There's a strange construction
on the summit of the promontory

00:15:18.307 --> 00:15:19.265 align:middle line:90%
with its massive walls.

00:15:19.265 --> 00:15:22.180 align:middle line:90%


00:15:22.180 --> 00:15:25.960 align:middle line:84%
It is perfectly round with three
concentric circles intersected

00:15:25.960 --> 00:15:29.020 align:middle line:84%
by walls radiating
out in spokes.

00:15:29.020 --> 00:15:31.360 align:middle line:10%
The circles are enclosed
by another square building

00:15:31.360 --> 00:15:33.550 align:middle line:10%
connected to the
foundations other square

00:15:33.550 --> 00:15:35.233 align:middle line:10%
or rectangular buildings.

00:15:35.233 --> 00:15:40.660 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:15:40.660 --> 00:15:43.750 align:middle line:10%
When we check the orientation
of the square building enclosing

00:15:43.750 --> 00:15:45.820 align:middle line:10%
the circular
construction, we found

00:15:45.820 --> 00:15:47.620 align:middle line:10%
that the corners were
perfectly aligned

00:15:47.620 --> 00:15:50.050 align:middle line:10%
with the cardinal
points of the compass,

00:15:50.050 --> 00:15:51.850 align:middle line:10%
and that the walls
intersecting the circles

00:15:51.850 --> 00:15:56.170 align:middle line:10%
run northeast, southeast,
northwest, and southwest--

00:15:56.170 --> 00:15:58.420 align:middle line:10%
ideal orientation for
determining the summer

00:15:58.420 --> 00:15:59.460 align:middle line:10%
and winter solstices.

00:15:59.460 --> 00:16:04.490 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16:04.490 --> 00:16:08.090 align:middle line:84%
Are these the ruins of an
astronomical observatory?

00:16:08.090 --> 00:16:10.550 align:middle line:84%
Who knows, but the concept
of the whole building

00:16:10.550 --> 00:16:12.320 align:middle line:90%
is extremely advanced.

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:14.000 align:middle line:84%
There are very few
similar examples

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:16.280 align:middle line:90%
in the whole of South America.

00:16:16.280 --> 00:16:21.560 align:middle line:84%
It is certainly very ancient,
older than the Incas.

00:16:21.560 --> 00:16:24.080 align:middle line:84%
Everything we'd
seen at Sacsayhuaman

00:16:24.080 --> 00:16:26.990 align:middle line:84%
seem to belong to a
remote age, a time we

00:16:26.990 --> 00:16:31.918 align:middle line:84%
have no human memory of, an
age lost in the mists of time.

00:16:31.918 --> 00:16:38.760 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:16:38.760 --> 00:16:41.130 align:middle line:90%
Is this a completely lost story?

00:16:41.130 --> 00:16:42.390 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps not.

00:16:42.390 --> 00:16:44.070 align:middle line:84%
Descendants of the
Incas still live

00:16:44.070 --> 00:16:46.380 align:middle line:84%
in the mountains and
remote pockets isolated

00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:48.540 align:middle line:84%
from white men,
groups which escaped

00:16:48.540 --> 00:16:50.530 align:middle line:90%
the fury of the conquistadores.

00:16:50.530 --> 00:16:52.890 align:middle line:84%
Their leaders are wise
old men, custodians

00:16:52.890 --> 00:16:54.240 align:middle line:90%
of ancient knowledge.

00:16:54.240 --> 00:16:56.010 align:middle line:90%
Some people have talked to them.

00:16:56.010 --> 00:16:58.790 align:middle line:84%
We were given a place,
Samana Wasi, and a name,

00:16:58.790 --> 00:17:00.760 align:middle line:90%
Anton Ponce de Leon.

00:17:00.760 --> 00:17:03.630 align:middle line:84%
Anton has written various
books on his experiences

00:17:03.630 --> 00:17:05.400 align:middle line:90%
in this ancient knowledge.

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:08.040 align:middle line:84%
Inspired by the teaching he
has founded and provided funds

00:17:08.040 --> 00:17:10.400 align:middle line:84%
for a community where,
with the help of his wife,

00:17:10.400 --> 00:17:13.740 align:middle line:84%
Regia, abandoned children and
old people are looked after--

00:17:13.740 --> 00:17:17.036 align:middle line:84%
the rest home, which
translated into Samana Wasi.

00:17:17.036 --> 00:17:21.220 align:middle line:10%
>> An old man explained this
knowledge to me in 10 to 15

00:17:21.220 --> 00:17:26.400 align:middle line:10%
minutes, using
very simple words.

00:17:26.400 --> 00:17:31.550 align:middle line:84%
But I was a very rational
man and I didn't believe him.

00:17:31.550 --> 00:17:35.270 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't accept that
the truth was so simple.

00:17:35.270 --> 00:17:37.860 align:middle line:84%
This knowledge is
still valid today.

00:17:37.860 --> 00:17:41.870 align:middle line:84%
It's still relevant,
despite the passing of time.

00:17:41.870 --> 00:17:46.140 align:middle line:84%
And I'm talking about
thousands of years.

00:17:46.140 --> 00:17:52.460 align:middle line:84%
This is an oral tradition, which
has been handed down, intact.

00:17:52.460 --> 00:17:57.602 align:middle line:84%
These enormous buildings with
their huge stone blocks--

00:17:57.602 --> 00:17:59.900 align:middle line:84%
yes, some people
say they were built

00:17:59.900 --> 00:18:04.940 align:middle line:84%
by beings from outer space,
but I don't think so.

00:18:04.940 --> 00:18:08.120 align:middle line:84%
All the buildings
in this world were

00:18:08.120 --> 00:18:13.760 align:middle line:84%
built by human
beings who certainly

00:18:13.760 --> 00:18:17.000 align:middle line:90%
had very wise teachers.

00:18:17.000 --> 00:18:20.090 align:middle line:84%
According to what I
learned, these teachers

00:18:20.090 --> 00:18:23.330 align:middle line:84%
came from a continent
which disappeared,

00:18:23.330 --> 00:18:25.820 align:middle line:90%
submerged by the Pacific.

00:18:25.820 --> 00:18:28.570 align:middle line:84%
It was the biggest
continent of all,

00:18:28.570 --> 00:18:33.650 align:middle line:84%
called Mu, sometimes
erroneously called Lemuria.

00:18:33.650 --> 00:18:36.500 align:middle line:84%
It is a continent
called Mu, a word that

00:18:36.500 --> 00:18:38.810 align:middle line:84%
comes from a very
ancient language

00:18:38.810 --> 00:18:41.670 align:middle line:90%
and means mother country.

00:18:41.670 --> 00:18:48.270 align:middle line:84%
The Murians, who for
us are the third race,

00:18:48.270 --> 00:18:53.340 align:middle line:84%
were very highly developed
physically, psychically,

00:18:53.340 --> 00:18:58.200 align:middle line:84%
and spiritually, a
level of development

00:18:58.200 --> 00:19:00.930 align:middle line:90%
we haven't achieved yet.

00:19:00.930 --> 00:19:07.620 align:middle line:84%
Moving large, heavy
objects represented

00:19:07.620 --> 00:19:11.580 align:middle line:90%
no particular problem for them.

00:19:11.580 --> 00:19:14.100 align:middle line:84%
These teachers
instructed the people

00:19:14.100 --> 00:19:20.540 align:middle line:84%
of the Andes, our
ancestors who built

00:19:20.540 --> 00:19:22.580 align:middle line:90%
these wonderful constructions.

00:19:22.580 --> 00:19:25.660 align:middle line:90%


00:19:25.660 --> 00:19:29.560 align:middle line:84%
We believe that the
Murian civilization

00:19:29.560 --> 00:19:33.580 align:middle line:84%
which had reached the Andes went
out west, too, towards Asia.

00:19:33.580 --> 00:19:36.990 align:middle line:90%


00:19:36.990 --> 00:19:41.785 align:middle line:84%
That's why we find the same
knowledge all over the world.

00:19:41.785 --> 00:19:43.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Is this the answer?

00:19:43.920 --> 00:19:47.880 align:middle line:84%
Was Mu a lost civilization we
have no memory of, the mother

00:19:47.880 --> 00:19:50.670 align:middle line:90%
of all known civilizations?

00:19:50.670 --> 00:19:52.740 align:middle line:84%
According to the wise
people of the Andes,

00:19:52.740 --> 00:19:55.260 align:middle line:84%
this is the key to many
mysteries of the past,

00:19:55.260 --> 00:19:57.990 align:middle line:84%
but we have other
clues to follow up.

00:19:57.990 --> 00:20:02.070 align:middle line:84%
Qenko is a few miles to
the east of Sacsayhuaman.

00:20:02.070 --> 00:20:06.060 align:middle line:84%
Its name could hardly be more
appropriate, given what we saw.

00:20:06.060 --> 00:20:08.750 align:middle line:90%
It means intersecting channels.

00:20:08.750 --> 00:20:11.700 align:middle line:84%
The huge rock, deeply
eroded around its base,

00:20:11.700 --> 00:20:14.670 align:middle line:84%
is carved into a very
strange shape at its summit.

00:20:14.670 --> 00:20:16.500 align:middle line:84%
It's chiseled,
carved, and molded

00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:19.620 align:middle line:84%
to create an absurd maze
of seemingly random shapes

00:20:19.620 --> 00:20:22.500 align:middle line:90%
with no apparent meaning.

00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:25.410 align:middle line:84%
It's incredible, it
almost makes you dizzy.

00:20:25.410 --> 00:20:27.720 align:middle line:84%
What's the meaning of
those short staircases,

00:20:27.720 --> 00:20:31.020 align:middle line:84%
those little platforms, those
channels, those balconies?

00:20:31.020 --> 00:20:33.970 align:middle line:84%
It's a real puzzle, impossible
to guess the answer.

00:20:33.970 --> 00:20:35.910 align:middle line:90%
Did the Incas make it?

00:20:35.910 --> 00:20:39.009 align:middle line:84%
Was it something to do with
their religious functions?

00:20:39.009 --> 00:20:40.800 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're told,
but we don't really

00:20:40.800 --> 00:20:42.170 align:middle line:90%
know what to think.

00:20:42.170 --> 00:20:43.680 align:middle line:84%
This disturbing
rock puzzle could

00:20:43.680 --> 00:20:47.430 align:middle line:84%
have been carved 500 years
ago, or 5,000, or 50,000.

00:20:47.430 --> 00:20:49.800 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:20:49.800 --> 00:20:52.045 align:middle line:84%
We've never seen
anything like it.

00:20:52.045 --> 00:20:53.170 align:middle line:90%
It seemed to have no logic.

00:20:53.170 --> 00:20:56.790 align:middle line:90%


00:20:56.790 --> 00:20:59.720 align:middle line:84%
There's a large opening at
the base of the massive rock.

00:20:59.720 --> 00:21:00.520 align:middle line:90%
We go in.

00:21:00.520 --> 00:21:04.570 align:middle line:90%


00:21:04.570 --> 00:21:07.720 align:middle line:84%
Inside is a fairly large
cave with a carved rock.

00:21:07.720 --> 00:21:10.230 align:middle line:90%


00:21:10.230 --> 00:21:11.910 align:middle line:90%
It looks like an altar.

00:21:11.910 --> 00:21:13.570 align:middle line:84%
Later we're told that
the Incas used it

00:21:13.570 --> 00:21:15.640 align:middle line:90%
for their religious ceremonies.

00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:18.872 align:middle line:84%
This explanation is certainly
in keeping with its appearance,

00:21:18.872 --> 00:21:20.830 align:middle line:84%
and that of the other
carved rocks in the cave.

00:21:20.830 --> 00:21:25.270 align:middle line:90%


00:21:25.270 --> 00:21:27.750 align:middle line:84%
But the incredible
maze outside looks

00:21:27.750 --> 00:21:32.970 align:middle line:84%
much older, designed and created
by other hands and other minds.

00:21:32.970 --> 00:21:35.580 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps the Incas had
found these strange ruins

00:21:35.580 --> 00:21:38.770 align:middle line:84%
and turned them into a
temple, believing them sacred.

00:21:38.770 --> 00:21:39.960 align:middle line:90%
That's one explanation.

00:21:39.960 --> 00:21:43.230 align:middle line:84%
The style and condition of
the stones seem to back it up.

00:21:43.230 --> 00:21:48.330 align:middle line:84%
The walls and monolith outside
look closer to the Inca style--

00:21:48.330 --> 00:21:50.460 align:middle line:90%
but not quite.

00:21:50.460 --> 00:21:53.280 align:middle line:84%
We know there's another
site a few miles away

00:21:53.280 --> 00:21:55.020 align:middle line:90%
with similar carved rock.

00:21:55.020 --> 00:21:56.940 align:middle line:84%
We have also found
out about a passage

00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:59.340 align:middle line:84%
which accesses a
network of seemingly

00:21:59.340 --> 00:22:02.340 align:middle line:90%
endless underground tunnels.

00:22:02.340 --> 00:22:06.930 align:middle line:84%
Many people have ventured in to
explore, never to emerge again.

00:22:06.930 --> 00:22:08.060 align:middle line:90%
It's called the X-Zone.

00:22:08.060 --> 00:22:11.810 align:middle line:90%


00:22:11.810 --> 00:22:13.580 align:middle line:90%
Here we get a real surprise.

00:22:13.580 --> 00:22:16.820 align:middle line:84%
The rock looks like an exact
copy of the one at Qenko,

00:22:16.820 --> 00:22:19.130 align:middle line:84%
the same patterns carved
in absurd positions.

00:22:19.130 --> 00:22:23.330 align:middle line:90%


00:22:23.330 --> 00:22:26.380 align:middle line:84%
Stairs that lead to nowhere,
completely off center.

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:29.070 align:middle line:90%
Why put steps in that position?

00:22:29.070 --> 00:22:32.700 align:middle line:84%
Were they for
working on, or what?

00:22:32.700 --> 00:22:34.500 align:middle line:84%
On one side, we
discover something

00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:38.010 align:middle line:84%
that looks like a throne, but
it's facing a wall of rock.

00:22:38.010 --> 00:22:39.840 align:middle line:90%
It's crazy.

00:22:39.840 --> 00:22:43.020 align:middle line:84%
The rocks at Qenko at the
X-Zone look out of place,

00:22:43.020 --> 00:22:45.690 align:middle line:84%
almost as if they were once
part of the same project which

00:22:45.690 --> 00:22:46.620 align:middle line:90%
no longer exists.

00:22:46.620 --> 00:22:49.612 align:middle line:90%


00:22:49.612 --> 00:22:51.820 align:middle line:84%
We search for the entrance
to the underground tunnels

00:22:51.820 --> 00:22:54.089 align:middle line:90%
and get a nasty surprise.

00:22:54.089 --> 00:22:55.630 align:middle line:84%
The local authorities
have blocked it

00:22:55.630 --> 00:23:00.790 align:middle line:84%
up to stop other people
wandering in and getting lost.

00:23:00.790 --> 00:23:03.400 align:middle line:84%
We feel like getting down to
work with picks and shovels

00:23:03.400 --> 00:23:06.190 align:middle line:84%
and opening it up again, but
we were repressed the urge

00:23:06.190 --> 00:23:07.570 align:middle line:90%
and decide to be patient.

00:23:07.570 --> 00:23:11.440 align:middle line:84%
The tunnels exist, all we have
to do now is find a way in.

00:23:11.440 --> 00:23:13.720 align:middle line:84%
These enigmatic sites
are very puzzling,

00:23:13.720 --> 00:23:15.820 align:middle line:84%
the discrepancies
are unsettling.

00:23:15.820 --> 00:23:18.370 align:middle line:84%
We meet someone who has
spoken to other wise man.

00:23:18.370 --> 00:23:20.890 align:middle line:84%
According to him, direct
descendants of the survivors

00:23:20.890 --> 00:23:22.510 align:middle line:90%
of the destruction of Mu.

00:23:22.510 --> 00:23:25.270 align:middle line:10%
They live in very remote areas
in the heart of the Amazon

00:23:25.270 --> 00:23:27.400 align:middle line:10%
basin, isolated
from white people.

00:23:27.400 --> 00:23:29.500 align:middle line:90%
His name is Ruben Iwaki Ordonez.

00:23:29.500 --> 00:23:32.050 align:middle line:84%
He has Indio blood in
his veins and he tells us

00:23:32.050 --> 00:23:34.990 align:middle line:84%
an amazing story about the
origins of the rocks at Qenko

00:23:34.990 --> 00:23:38.030 align:middle line:90%
and the X-Zone.

00:23:38.030 --> 00:23:42.400 align:middle line:10%
>> Right here where the
city of Cusco is now,

00:23:42.400 --> 00:23:44.470 align:middle line:10%
in ancient times
there was a lake.

00:23:44.470 --> 00:23:47.720 align:middle line:90%


00:23:47.720 --> 00:23:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And under this
lake, under its bed,

00:23:52.100 --> 00:24:02.750 align:middle line:84%
there was an underground temple,
about 250 feet underground.

00:24:02.750 --> 00:24:06.770 align:middle line:84%
The wise ones lived down
there, the ancient ones who

00:24:06.770 --> 00:24:09.410 align:middle line:90%
governed the continent wisely.

00:24:09.410 --> 00:24:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And the entrance
to this place was

00:24:11.480 --> 00:24:16.460 align:middle line:84%
on a hill, the same hill that's
called Sacsayhuaman today.

00:24:16.460 --> 00:24:19.310 align:middle line:90%
That's where the entrance was.

00:24:19.310 --> 00:24:25.290 align:middle line:84%
After 10,000 years, there was
a cataclysm on the planet.

00:24:25.290 --> 00:24:30.770 align:middle line:84%
It destroyed the temple, and
the lake above it flooded.

00:24:30.770 --> 00:24:37.030 align:middle line:84%
This cataclysm wasn't an
earthquake, it was much more.

00:24:37.030 --> 00:24:39.780 align:middle line:90%
There were volcanic eruptions--

00:24:39.780 --> 00:24:40.580 align:middle line:90%
here, too.

00:24:40.580 --> 00:24:44.330 align:middle line:90%


00:24:44.330 --> 00:24:46.910 align:middle line:84%
Here, where the
temple was, there

00:24:46.910 --> 00:24:51.020 align:middle line:84%
was a volcanic eruption,
a terrible explosion.

00:24:51.020 --> 00:24:53.970 align:middle line:90%


00:24:53.970 --> 00:25:00.040 align:middle line:10%
In Sacsayhuaman, there's an area
where the lava has solidified.

00:25:00.040 --> 00:25:03.240 align:middle line:90%


00:25:03.240 --> 00:25:07.110 align:middle line:84%
But that explosion produced
fragments of exploding rock,

00:25:07.110 --> 00:25:10.550 align:middle line:90%
too, burning pieces of rock.

00:25:10.550 --> 00:25:14.290 align:middle line:90%


00:25:14.290 --> 00:25:18.490 align:middle line:10%
The force of the explosion
shattered the rooms

00:25:18.490 --> 00:25:23.980 align:middle line:10%
of the temple, and fragments
were thrown into the air

00:25:23.980 --> 00:25:28.480 align:middle line:10%
and fell here, there,
and everywhere.

00:25:28.480 --> 00:25:30.870 align:middle line:84%
There's one that
nowadays is called Qenko.

00:25:30.870 --> 00:25:33.720 align:middle line:90%


00:25:33.720 --> 00:25:36.290 align:middle line:90%
The Incas found it like that.

00:25:36.290 --> 00:25:40.120 align:middle line:90%


00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:42.250 align:middle line:84%
They found these
wonderful constructions

00:25:42.250 --> 00:25:46.320 align:middle line:84%
and they used them for
their religious ceremonies.

00:25:46.320 --> 00:25:49.050 align:middle line:90%


00:25:49.050 --> 00:25:52.860 align:middle line:84%
Because they realized
how important they were,

00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:54.370 align:middle line:90%
they knew where they came from.

00:25:54.370 --> 00:25:58.780 align:middle line:90%


00:25:58.780 --> 00:26:02.920 align:middle line:84%
There are other fragments as
big as this room in an area

00:26:02.920 --> 00:26:04.810 align:middle line:90%
near the solidified lava.

00:26:04.810 --> 00:26:07.690 align:middle line:90%


00:26:07.690 --> 00:26:13.510 align:middle line:84%
There, you can see
upside-down staircases.

00:26:13.510 --> 00:26:17.510 align:middle line:84%
Well, these fragments
came up from underground

00:26:17.510 --> 00:26:21.640 align:middle line:84%
when the disaster
happened, and they fell.

00:26:21.640 --> 00:26:26.530 align:middle line:84%
They fell haphazardly,
upside-down.

00:26:26.530 --> 00:26:31.081 align:middle line:84%
And this shows that they were
part of what was underground.

00:26:31.081 --> 00:26:33.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Once again, ancient
traditions insist

00:26:33.670 --> 00:26:36.490 align:middle line:84%
on the existence of once great
civilizations which have now

00:26:36.490 --> 00:26:40.060 align:middle line:84%
disappeared, and Cusco still has
some mysteries in store for us.

00:26:40.060 --> 00:26:43.650 align:middle line:90%


00:26:43.650 --> 00:26:45.450 align:middle line:84%
The most sacred and
important temple

00:26:45.450 --> 00:26:47.970 align:middle line:84%
in the whole of the Inca
empire was at Cusco.

00:26:47.970 --> 00:26:49.670 align:middle line:84%
It was dedicated
to their culture,

00:26:49.670 --> 00:26:53.440 align:middle line:84%
and it was called Coricancha,
or the Golden Enclosure.

00:26:53.440 --> 00:26:58.150 align:middle line:84%
The Spanish built Santo
Domingo Cathedral on its ruins.

00:26:58.150 --> 00:26:59.780 align:middle line:84%
But the ancient
walls can still be

00:26:59.780 --> 00:27:02.810 align:middle line:84%
seen, both from inside and
outside the latter day colonial

00:27:02.810 --> 00:27:03.890 align:middle line:90%
church.

00:27:03.890 --> 00:27:07.970 align:middle line:84%
The walls are still imposing
and very cleverly crafted.

00:27:07.970 --> 00:27:09.800 align:middle line:84%
But the stones themselves
are much smaller

00:27:09.800 --> 00:27:14.580 align:middle line:84%
than any other structures we
have visited, more a building

00:27:14.580 --> 00:27:18.310 align:middle line:84%
that Inca architects
might have designed.

00:27:18.310 --> 00:27:21.130 align:middle line:84%
There are tunnels
under the church.

00:27:21.130 --> 00:27:25.680 align:middle line:84%
A story tells of how some
boys got lost in them in 1920.

00:27:25.680 --> 00:27:27.370 align:middle line:84%
After a whole week,
only one of them

00:27:27.370 --> 00:27:30.060 align:middle line:84%
re-emerged, injured
and confused.

00:27:30.060 --> 00:27:32.730 align:middle line:84%
He died soon afterwards,
clutching a solid gold

00:27:32.730 --> 00:27:34.650 align:middle line:90%
cob of corn.

00:27:34.650 --> 00:27:37.110 align:middle line:84%
There are no written records
to confirm the story,

00:27:37.110 --> 00:27:40.770 align:middle line:84%
but the people of Cusco
assure us it's true.

00:27:40.770 --> 00:27:43.110 align:middle line:84%
We managed to get permission
to visit the digs made

00:27:43.110 --> 00:27:45.330 align:middle line:84%
by other researchers
who had been trying

00:27:45.330 --> 00:27:47.940 align:middle line:84%
to unravel the puzzle of
the mysterious tunnels

00:27:47.940 --> 00:27:49.680 align:middle line:90%
and climb down under the church.

00:27:49.680 --> 00:27:56.160 align:middle line:90%


00:27:56.160 --> 00:27:59.730 align:middle line:84%
We follow the tunnel for a
while, but it brought up short.

00:27:59.730 --> 00:28:00.920 align:middle line:90%
The tunnel is blocked.

00:28:00.920 --> 00:28:06.470 align:middle line:90%


00:28:06.470 --> 00:28:08.840 align:middle line:84%
Later, we're told that the
excavations were stopped

00:28:08.840 --> 00:28:11.150 align:middle line:84%
because of the risk of
undermining the foundations

00:28:11.150 --> 00:28:12.050 align:middle line:90%
of the church above.

00:28:12.050 --> 00:28:14.620 align:middle line:90%


00:28:14.620 --> 00:28:16.480 align:middle line:84%
We wonder whether the
Coricancha tunnels

00:28:16.480 --> 00:28:19.990 align:middle line:84%
led to a more impressive network
of underground tunnels, perhaps

00:28:19.990 --> 00:28:24.280 align:middle line:84%
those that connected Cusco,
Sacsayhuaman, and other places

00:28:24.280 --> 00:28:25.330 align:middle line:90%
even further away.

00:28:25.330 --> 00:28:28.700 align:middle line:90%


00:28:28.700 --> 00:28:31.180 align:middle line:84%
But we'll have to wait for
answers to these questions.

00:28:31.180 --> 00:28:35.500 align:middle line:90%


00:28:35.500 --> 00:28:38.340 align:middle line:84%
The fact is, the tunnels
exist and their existence

00:28:38.340 --> 00:28:40.675 align:middle line:84%
is backed up by
ancient traditions.

00:28:40.675 --> 00:28:44.000 align:middle line:90%


00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:47.160 align:middle line:10%
>> Traditionally, the tunnels
are supposed to have gone from

00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:50.910 align:middle line:10%
Cusco towards Quito in Ecuador.

00:28:50.910 --> 00:28:53.160 align:middle line:84%
And from the south,
they went towards what

00:28:53.160 --> 00:28:56.820 align:middle line:84%
is today Bolivia, towards
Chile, towards the forest,

00:28:56.820 --> 00:28:59.880 align:middle line:90%
towards Brazil.

00:28:59.880 --> 00:29:01.316 align:middle line:90%
They went everywhere.

00:29:01.316 --> 00:29:04.190 align:middle line:90%


00:29:04.190 --> 00:29:11.710 align:middle line:84%
Unfortunately, some of them were
blocked up for safety reasons

00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:13.700 align:middle line:90%
when they were discovered.

00:29:13.700 --> 00:29:19.820 align:middle line:84%
So nowadays, it's very
difficult to find the entrances.

00:29:19.820 --> 00:29:23.490 align:middle line:84%
I know, I'm sure,
that they exist.

00:29:23.490 --> 00:29:29.070 align:middle line:84%
I saw some of them with my
father when I was a child.

00:29:29.070 --> 00:29:31.730 align:middle line:84%
And I know that
there are tunnels

00:29:31.730 --> 00:29:34.502 align:middle line:90%
under the Catholic churches.

00:29:34.502 --> 00:29:38.120 align:middle line:84%
>> We discover that another
church in Cusco has tunnels,

00:29:38.120 --> 00:29:41.060 align:middle line:90%
the Church of the Jesuits.

00:29:41.060 --> 00:29:45.140 align:middle line:84%
It was built in 1576 on the
foundations of the Amarucancha

00:29:45.140 --> 00:29:48.175 align:middle line:84%
Church, the royal palace of
the Inca ruler, Huayna Capac.

00:29:48.175 --> 00:29:51.320 align:middle line:90%


00:29:51.320 --> 00:29:54.290 align:middle line:84%
When the Spanish arrived,
Huayna Capac's two sons,

00:29:54.290 --> 00:29:57.530 align:middle line:84%
Huascar and Atahualpa,
were waging a civil war

00:29:57.530 --> 00:29:59.179 align:middle line:90%
for control of the empire.

00:29:59.179 --> 00:30:01.220 align:middle line:84%
This helped the Spanish
conquer the Inca kingdom.

00:30:01.220 --> 00:30:04.130 align:middle line:90%


00:30:04.130 --> 00:30:07.640 align:middle line:84%
The church houses some
important works of art.

00:30:07.640 --> 00:30:09.260 align:middle line:10%
One of the most
important pieces is

00:30:09.260 --> 00:30:12.500 align:middle line:10%
the altar carved in cedar
wood and covered in gold.

00:30:12.500 --> 00:30:15.130 align:middle line:84%
It was by the Italian
sculptor, Bernardo Bitti.

00:30:15.130 --> 00:30:20.300 align:middle line:90%


00:30:20.300 --> 00:30:22.880 align:middle line:84%
After long talks, we
managed to get permission

00:30:22.880 --> 00:30:25.590 align:middle line:84%
to explore underground
this church, too.

00:30:25.590 --> 00:30:30.490 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:30:30.490 --> 00:30:37.350 align:middle line:90%


00:30:37.350 --> 00:30:39.980 align:middle line:84%
There's a small,
beautifully decorated chapel

00:30:39.980 --> 00:30:40.780 align:middle line:90%
under the altar.

00:30:40.780 --> 00:30:50.410 align:middle line:90%


00:30:50.410 --> 00:30:53.500 align:middle line:84%
This is where the trapdoor
that accesses the tunnels is.

00:30:53.500 --> 00:30:56.020 align:middle line:90%


00:30:56.020 --> 00:30:58.942 align:middle line:84%
The heavy cover hasn't been
lifted for a long time.

00:30:58.942 --> 00:31:03.862 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:03.862 --> 00:31:21.580 align:middle line:90%


00:31:21.580 --> 00:31:24.280 align:middle line:84%
We're very excited
as we get ready.

00:31:24.280 --> 00:31:26.140 align:middle line:84%
This is the first
time cameras have been

00:31:26.140 --> 00:31:27.922 align:middle line:90%
allowed to film the tunnels.

00:31:27.922 --> 00:31:32.842 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:32.842 --> 00:31:40.740 align:middle line:90%


00:31:40.740 --> 00:31:45.320 align:middle line:84%
The entrance is small and
difficult to get into.

00:31:45.320 --> 00:31:50.220 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:50.220 --> 00:31:56.610 align:middle line:90%


00:31:56.610 --> 00:31:59.890 align:middle line:84%
Once we manage to climb down,
we get a disappointment.

00:31:59.890 --> 00:32:02.430 align:middle line:84%
The tunnels are blocked
after only a few meters.

00:32:02.430 --> 00:32:04.140 align:middle line:84%
The ecclesiastical
authorities ordered

00:32:04.140 --> 00:32:06.240 align:middle line:84%
them to be blocked
for security reasons.

00:32:06.240 --> 00:32:08.730 align:middle line:84%
The tunnels run under
the city, and in the past

00:32:08.730 --> 00:32:12.870 align:middle line:84%
have been used by thieves
as a way into the church.

00:32:12.870 --> 00:32:15.730 align:middle line:84%
But once more, they confirm
that the Incas' sacred places

00:32:15.730 --> 00:32:17.355 align:middle line:84%
were connected by a
network of tunnels.

00:32:17.355 --> 00:32:21.290 align:middle line:90%


00:32:21.290 --> 00:32:23.670 align:middle line:90%
Did the Incas build them?

00:32:23.670 --> 00:32:26.180 align:middle line:84%
Ancient tradition
believes not, and we

00:32:26.180 --> 00:32:30.440 align:middle line:84%
find echoes in the chronicles of
the conquistadores themselves.

00:32:30.440 --> 00:32:36.980 align:middle line:84%
In 1571, Juan Polo de Ondegardo
wrote, "The city of Cusco

00:32:36.980 --> 00:32:39.530 align:middle line:84%
was the home and
residence of the gods.

00:32:39.530 --> 00:32:41.975 align:middle line:84%
Every fountain, well, and
wall concealed a mystery."

00:32:41.975 --> 00:32:47.580 align:middle line:90%


00:32:47.580 --> 00:32:50.990 align:middle line:84%
We leave Cusco on the trail
of more Peruvian mysteries.

00:32:50.990 --> 00:32:55.830 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:32:55.830 --> 00:33:00.670 align:middle line:90%


00:33:00.670 --> 00:33:03.280 align:middle line:84%
The fortress of
Ollantaytambo dominates

00:33:03.280 --> 00:33:05.050 align:middle line:90%
the Valley of Urubamba.

00:33:05.050 --> 00:33:08.180 align:middle line:84%
Clinging to a hill
about 300 feet high,

00:33:08.180 --> 00:33:09.730 align:middle line:84%
it was the Incas'
main fortification

00:33:09.730 --> 00:33:11.800 align:middle line:90%
to defend the Sacred Valley.

00:33:11.800 --> 00:33:13.480 align:middle line:84%
It was here that
Pizarro experienced

00:33:13.480 --> 00:33:15.640 align:middle line:84%
one of his few defeats
during his campaign

00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:18.610 align:middle line:84%
to conquer the huge
empire of the sun.

00:33:18.610 --> 00:33:21.280 align:middle line:84%
Characterized by its
terraces used for farming,

00:33:21.280 --> 00:33:25.480 align:middle line:84%
the settlement developed up
to the summit of the hill.

00:33:25.480 --> 00:33:27.330 align:middle line:84%
It was an important
military, religious,

00:33:27.330 --> 00:33:30.210 align:middle line:84%
and agricultural
center, about 60 miles

00:33:30.210 --> 00:33:32.880 align:middle line:90%
to the northwest of Cusco.

00:33:32.880 --> 00:33:34.950 align:middle line:84%
About 2/3 of the way
up the steep steps

00:33:34.950 --> 00:33:37.530 align:middle line:84%
that lead to the top of the
hill, the familiar walls

00:33:37.530 --> 00:33:40.710 align:middle line:84%
appear with their usual
astonishing craftsmanship.

00:33:40.710 --> 00:33:42.420 align:middle line:84%
Extremely large,
heavy, skillfully

00:33:42.420 --> 00:33:45.690 align:middle line:84%
worked polygonal stones
fitting perfectly together

00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:49.820 align:middle line:84%
with no mortar or any
other type of cement.

00:33:49.820 --> 00:33:53.420 align:middle line:84%
Again, we wonder,
is this Inca work?

00:33:53.420 --> 00:33:55.900 align:middle line:90%
The archaeologists say it is.

00:33:55.900 --> 00:33:59.220 align:middle line:84%
But on one wall we find a
stretch that has been repaired.

00:33:59.220 --> 00:34:01.130 align:middle line:84%
It must have been
done by the Incas.

00:34:01.130 --> 00:34:02.930 align:middle line:84%
But strangely, the
repair work has

00:34:02.930 --> 00:34:05.060 align:middle line:84%
been carried out using
much smaller stones,

00:34:05.060 --> 00:34:08.050 align:middle line:84%
and the level of
craftsmanship is much rougher.

00:34:08.050 --> 00:34:09.050 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:34:09.050 --> 00:34:11.270 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps the Inca architects
had forgotten their one

00:34:11.270 --> 00:34:12.980 align:middle line:90%
sophisticated techniques.

00:34:12.980 --> 00:34:16.100 align:middle line:84%
Or, were the original
builders not Incas?

00:34:16.100 --> 00:34:18.960 align:middle line:84%
That seems to be the
most likely answer.

00:34:18.960 --> 00:34:21.409 align:middle line:84%
There are a row of
10 trapezoidal niches

00:34:21.409 --> 00:34:24.219 align:middle line:84%
on the wall of the terrace where
the main entrance once was.

00:34:24.219 --> 00:34:27.070 align:middle line:90%


00:34:27.070 --> 00:34:30.280 align:middle line:84%
The joints are incredible,
with absurd angles.

00:34:30.280 --> 00:34:32.150 align:middle line:90%
They look almost ironical.

00:34:32.150 --> 00:34:34.270 align:middle line:84%
Did they have a
practical purpose?

00:34:34.270 --> 00:34:36.429 align:middle line:84%
Or were they're just showing
off the craftsmanship

00:34:36.429 --> 00:34:37.229 align:middle line:90%
of the builders?

00:34:37.229 --> 00:34:40.750 align:middle line:90%


00:34:40.750 --> 00:34:42.580 align:middle line:84%
As we climb higher,
the walls still

00:34:42.580 --> 00:34:44.694 align:middle line:84%
show the same level of
incredible workmanship

00:34:44.694 --> 00:34:45.860 align:middle line:90%
as the ones we've just seen.

00:34:45.860 --> 00:34:52.510 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:34:52.510 --> 00:34:54.400 align:middle line:84%
On top of the hill,
we find the ruins

00:34:54.400 --> 00:34:56.860 align:middle line:84%
of the houses which once
belonged to the Inca priests

00:34:56.860 --> 00:35:00.740 align:middle line:84%
and nobles, while the populace
lived in houses further down.

00:35:00.740 --> 00:35:05.050 align:middle line:90%


00:35:05.050 --> 00:35:09.090 align:middle line:84%
There are other remains on the
slopes of the hill in front.

00:35:09.090 --> 00:35:11.070 align:middle line:84%
Archaeologists say
that they were once

00:35:11.070 --> 00:35:13.450 align:middle line:90%
grain storage warehouses.

00:35:13.450 --> 00:35:15.310 align:middle line:84%
But although they're
very interesting,

00:35:15.310 --> 00:35:19.440 align:middle line:84%
our attention is attracted
by something else.

00:35:19.440 --> 00:35:22.785 align:middle line:84%
On the top of the hill, a series
of huge red porphyry monoliths

00:35:22.785 --> 00:35:25.650 align:middle line:84%
form a mad puzzle,
lying scattered around

00:35:25.650 --> 00:35:28.320 align:middle line:84%
on the ground in no apparent
order, some of them weighing

00:35:28.320 --> 00:35:31.556 align:middle line:90%
dozens of tons.

00:35:31.556 --> 00:35:34.120 align:middle line:84%
Some are accurately
carved, others

00:35:34.120 --> 00:35:35.410 align:middle line:90%
are obviously unfinished.

00:35:35.410 --> 00:35:40.190 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:35:40.190 --> 00:35:43.060 align:middle line:90%


00:35:43.060 --> 00:35:46.810 align:middle line:84%
An amazing structure rises
out of this chaotic scene.

00:35:46.810 --> 00:35:49.330 align:middle line:84%
Six enormous monoliths
perfectly aligned

00:35:49.330 --> 00:35:52.990 align:middle line:84%
along a southeasterly vector,
and perhaps uniquely separated

00:35:52.990 --> 00:35:56.020 align:middle line:84%
by spaces in the same
stone, a unique example

00:35:56.020 --> 00:35:59.090 align:middle line:90%
of craftsmanship.

00:35:59.090 --> 00:36:02.840 align:middle line:84%
Red porphyry is a very hard
stone, as heavy as granite.

00:36:02.840 --> 00:36:07.190 align:middle line:84%
The monoliths are about 13 feet
high, six and 1/2 feet wide,

00:36:07.190 --> 00:36:09.430 align:middle line:90%
and three to six feet thick.

00:36:09.430 --> 00:36:12.280 align:middle line:90%
They weigh from 25 to 50 tons.

00:36:12.280 --> 00:36:14.290 align:middle line:84%
They were quarried
from a nearby mountain,

00:36:14.290 --> 00:36:16.480 align:middle line:84%
so obviously they were
cut from the rock face,

00:36:16.480 --> 00:36:20.290 align:middle line:84%
taken down into the valley,
and then dragged 328 feet up

00:36:20.290 --> 00:36:21.730 align:middle line:90%
to their destination.

00:36:21.730 --> 00:36:24.430 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:36:24.430 --> 00:36:27.250 align:middle line:84%
Archaeologists mentioned
thousands of workers, ropes,

00:36:27.250 --> 00:36:29.740 align:middle line:84%
tree trunks, and potatoes
used as lubricant

00:36:29.740 --> 00:36:32.350 align:middle line:84%
to help the massive
monoliths slide.

00:36:32.350 --> 00:36:35.080 align:middle line:90%
That's right, potatoes.

00:36:35.080 --> 00:36:37.180 align:middle line:84%
The structure is
obviously incomplete,

00:36:37.180 --> 00:36:39.580 align:middle line:84%
as the blocks scatter
haphazardly around the summit

00:36:39.580 --> 00:36:40.420 align:middle line:90%
confirm.

00:36:40.420 --> 00:36:43.060 align:middle line:84%
But nobody knows what
its intended use was

00:36:43.060 --> 00:36:45.190 align:middle line:90%
or why it was never finished.

00:36:45.190 --> 00:36:48.760 align:middle line:84%
Another enigma puzzles us in
the midst of so many mysteries,

00:36:48.760 --> 00:36:51.910 align:middle line:84%
a symbol carved on
one of the monoliths.

00:36:51.910 --> 00:36:55.000 align:middle line:84%
A pyramid rising in
steps, the same symbol

00:36:55.000 --> 00:36:58.040 align:middle line:90%
also found in Egypt.

00:36:58.040 --> 00:36:59.360 align:middle line:90%
Is it just a coincidence?

00:36:59.360 --> 00:37:01.610 align:middle line:84%
The Incas certainly had no
knowledge of the Egyptians,

00:37:01.610 --> 00:37:03.380 align:middle line:84%
but could both
civilizations have been

00:37:03.380 --> 00:37:05.270 align:middle line:90%
inspired by the same matrix?

00:37:05.270 --> 00:37:07.010 align:middle line:84%
In his book,
"Operation Fawcett,"

00:37:07.010 --> 00:37:10.070 align:middle line:84%
the legendary explorer
Colonel Percy Fawcett wrote,

00:37:10.070 --> 00:37:12.500 align:middle line:84%
"The Incas inherited
their fortresses in cities

00:37:12.500 --> 00:37:14.470 align:middle line:90%
from an earlier civilization."

00:37:14.470 --> 00:37:16.760 align:middle line:84%
And Garcilaso de la
Vega, in his chronicles,

00:37:16.760 --> 00:37:19.280 align:middle line:84%
tells us how they had been
erected in the first age,

00:37:19.280 --> 00:37:20.540 align:middle line:90%
before the Incas.

00:37:20.540 --> 00:37:22.940 align:middle line:84%
The first age--
what does it mean?

00:37:22.940 --> 00:37:25.520 align:middle line:84%
Was it the age when
the gods could fly?

00:37:25.520 --> 00:37:28.340 align:middle line:84%
The age when the survivors of
an ancient, highly developed

00:37:28.340 --> 00:37:30.000 align:middle line:90%
civilization settled in Peru?

00:37:30.000 --> 00:37:32.680 align:middle line:90%


00:37:32.680 --> 00:37:36.610 align:middle line:10%
>> We have evidence of
this because here in Peru

00:37:36.610 --> 00:37:39.020 align:middle line:10%
we've studied the
pre-Inca nations.

00:37:39.020 --> 00:37:41.760 align:middle line:90%


00:37:41.760 --> 00:37:47.830 align:middle line:84%
10,000 years ago, there
was the Chimu civilization,

00:37:47.830 --> 00:37:51.840 align:middle line:90%
which means those from Mu.

00:37:51.840 --> 00:37:58.060 align:middle line:84%
Further south, there was the
Moche civilization, sometimes

00:37:58.060 --> 00:38:00.070 align:middle line:84%
called Mochica, but
the correct name

00:38:00.070 --> 00:38:03.990 align:middle line:84%
is Moche, descendants
of Mu, coming from Mu.

00:38:03.990 --> 00:38:08.840 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:38:08.840 --> 00:38:18.055 align:middle line:90%


00:38:18.055 --> 00:38:22.330 align:middle line:84%
>> We leave from the little
station at Ollantaytambo.

00:38:22.330 --> 00:38:25.000 align:middle line:84%
The train winds its slow
way next to the river

00:38:25.000 --> 00:38:28.510 align:middle line:84%
through the Urubamba Valley,
the Sacred Valley of the Incas.

00:38:28.510 --> 00:38:33.160 align:middle line:90%


00:38:33.160 --> 00:38:36.610 align:middle line:84%
The countryside is
interesting, harsh, and wild.

00:38:36.610 --> 00:38:38.260 align:middle line:84%
It gets greener
the further we go.

00:38:38.260 --> 00:38:42.950 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:38:42.950 --> 00:38:45.300 align:middle line:90%


00:38:45.300 --> 00:38:48.490 align:middle line:10%
Finally, we arrive in
Machu Picchu, sacred myth

00:38:48.490 --> 00:38:49.490 align:middle line:10%
of the past and present.

00:38:49.490 --> 00:38:53.440 align:middle line:90%


00:38:53.440 --> 00:38:57.960 align:middle line:84%
We get over the station
in Aguas Calientes.

00:38:57.960 --> 00:39:00.060 align:middle line:84%
This little town is at
the foot of the mountain

00:39:00.060 --> 00:39:03.830 align:middle line:84%
where the lost city of
the Incas is sighted.

00:39:03.830 --> 00:39:06.300 align:middle line:84%
It has grown rapidly
in a chaotic fashion,

00:39:06.300 --> 00:39:08.940 align:middle line:84%
thanks to the influx of tourists
from all over the world.

00:39:08.940 --> 00:39:13.188 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:13.188 --> 00:39:16.980 align:middle line:90%


00:39:16.980 --> 00:39:19.080 align:middle line:84%
We shoulder the equipment
we need to film,

00:39:19.080 --> 00:39:22.200 align:middle line:84%
and set off towards the
archaeological site.

00:39:22.200 --> 00:39:24.490 align:middle line:84%
The road we take
is the steepest.

00:39:24.490 --> 00:39:27.180 align:middle line:84%
It leads to one of the highest
points which dominate the city.

00:39:27.180 --> 00:39:30.210 align:middle line:90%


00:39:30.210 --> 00:39:32.190 align:middle line:84%
The climb is tiring,
we still haven't

00:39:32.190 --> 00:39:34.170 align:middle line:84%
gotten acclimatized
to the altitude here.

00:39:34.170 --> 00:39:38.508 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:38.508 --> 00:39:45.760 align:middle line:90%


00:39:45.760 --> 00:39:49.210 align:middle line:84%
But the magic of the place
has already enthralled us.

00:39:49.210 --> 00:39:52.750 align:middle line:84%
We're impatient, we can't wait
to see the legendary monuments

00:39:52.750 --> 00:39:55.480 align:middle line:84%
of one of the most fascinating
cities of the ancient world.

00:39:55.480 --> 00:39:59.827 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:59.827 --> 00:40:04.180 align:middle line:90%


00:40:04.180 --> 00:40:07.270 align:middle line:84%
Machu Picchu, the
lost of the Incas,

00:40:07.270 --> 00:40:11.200 align:middle line:84%
emerged from the
mists of time in 1911.

00:40:11.200 --> 00:40:13.330 align:middle line:84%
The American explorer,
Hiram Bingham,

00:40:13.330 --> 00:40:17.440 align:middle line:84%
professor at Yale University,
is the author of the discovery.

00:40:17.440 --> 00:40:20.890 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, the
Peruvian archaeologist Agustin

00:40:20.890 --> 00:40:24.410 align:middle line:84%
Lizarraga had discovered the
ruins before him in 1902.

00:40:24.410 --> 00:40:26.230 align:middle line:84%
And two families
of campesinas were

00:40:26.230 --> 00:40:28.790 align:middle line:84%
found living there, farming
the ancient terraces left

00:40:28.790 --> 00:40:29.590 align:middle line:90%
by the Incas.

00:40:29.590 --> 00:40:33.260 align:middle line:90%


00:40:33.260 --> 00:40:34.880 align:middle line:10%
Bingham had the
merit of studying

00:40:34.880 --> 00:40:36.800 align:middle line:10%
the site scientifically
and telling

00:40:36.800 --> 00:40:41.415 align:middle line:10%
the world about this
amazing urban structure.

00:40:41.415 --> 00:40:44.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Without taking any
merit away from Bingham,

00:40:44.010 --> 00:40:46.740 align:middle line:84%
he was the one who made
Machu Picchu world famous.

00:40:46.740 --> 00:40:51.210 align:middle line:10%
But it was the Peruvians who
guided him to Machu Picchu.

00:40:51.210 --> 00:40:54.300 align:middle line:90%
That's important to remember.

00:40:54.300 --> 00:40:56.190 align:middle line:84%
There were people here
before, and people

00:40:56.190 --> 00:41:00.795 align:middle line:84%
came to Machu Picchu from Cusco
many years before Mr. Bingham.

00:41:00.795 --> 00:41:02.660 align:middle line:90%
>> When was it built?

00:41:02.660 --> 00:41:04.220 align:middle line:90%
What was it for?

00:41:04.220 --> 00:41:06.440 align:middle line:90%
Was it a fortified settlement?

00:41:06.440 --> 00:41:09.290 align:middle line:84%
A refuge for the noble
Inca class, or a city

00:41:09.290 --> 00:41:11.280 align:middle line:84%
dedicated to the
cult of the gods?

00:41:11.280 --> 00:41:14.330 align:middle line:84%
There are many theories,
but no short answers.

00:41:14.330 --> 00:41:15.950 align:middle line:90%
Yet the stones speak.

00:41:15.950 --> 00:41:19.010 align:middle line:84%
Machu Picchu is a silent
voice with many tales to tell,

00:41:19.010 --> 00:41:22.310 align:middle line:90%
if you listen carefully.

00:41:22.310 --> 00:41:27.250 align:middle line:84%
Machu Picchu, a saga in stone
at 7,800 feet above sea level,

00:41:27.250 --> 00:41:30.110 align:middle line:84%
is perfectly integrated
with its surroundings.

00:41:30.110 --> 00:41:33.290 align:middle line:84%
So much so that it looks
almost like a natural feature,

00:41:33.290 --> 00:41:35.750 align:middle line:84%
rather than a man-made
construction, the logic

00:41:35.750 --> 00:41:38.180 align:middle line:90%
behind so many great works.

00:41:38.180 --> 00:41:42.800 align:middle line:84%
The sacred rock reproduces the
profile of the nearby mountain.

00:41:42.800 --> 00:41:45.920 align:middle line:10%
In a fantastic play
of light and shadows,

00:41:45.920 --> 00:41:49.010 align:middle line:10%
the profile of an Indios emerges
from the shape of the mountains

00:41:49.010 --> 00:41:50.540 align:middle line:10%
against the skyline.

00:41:50.540 --> 00:41:54.550 align:middle line:10%
An incredible coincidence?

00:41:54.550 --> 00:41:57.460 align:middle line:84%
In the Condor Temple,
sculpted in natural elements

00:41:57.460 --> 00:42:01.810 align:middle line:84%
blend to bring the sacred animal
to life, its wings of stone

00:42:01.810 --> 00:42:05.700 align:middle line:84%
capture a moment of
flight for all eternity.

00:42:05.700 --> 00:42:09.930 align:middle line:84%
The Water Temple, water another
sacred element for the Incas.

00:42:09.930 --> 00:42:14.340 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:42:14.340 --> 00:42:20.230 align:middle line:90%


00:42:20.230 --> 00:42:22.070 align:middle line:90%
The mysterious Mortar Room.

00:42:22.070 --> 00:42:26.370 align:middle line:84%
It's in what is known
as the Industrial Area.

00:42:26.370 --> 00:42:28.470 align:middle line:84%
The Incas were believed
to have died material

00:42:28.470 --> 00:42:31.410 align:middle line:84%
in the two rocks shaped like
mortars, material they then

00:42:31.410 --> 00:42:35.800 align:middle line:84%
dried in the cylinders
protruding from the walls.

00:42:35.800 --> 00:42:40.740 align:middle line:84%
But is this the
right explanation?

00:42:40.740 --> 00:42:43.440 align:middle line:84%
Magical Machu Picchu,
scattered fragments

00:42:43.440 --> 00:42:47.400 align:middle line:90%
from a lost, arcane world.

00:42:47.400 --> 00:42:48.960 align:middle line:10%
The houses of the
ordinary people

00:42:48.960 --> 00:42:50.880 align:middle line:10%
were near the
agricultural sector.

00:42:50.880 --> 00:42:53.700 align:middle line:84%
With its barns and
characteristic terraces,

00:42:53.700 --> 00:42:58.140 align:middle line:84%
the houses are stone
built, small, and simple.

00:42:58.140 --> 00:43:00.000 align:middle line:84%
Once through the main
gates of the city,

00:43:00.000 --> 00:43:02.310 align:middle line:84%
the path winds through
some narrow streets,

00:43:02.310 --> 00:43:06.630 align:middle line:84%
and then leads to a
strangely shaped building.

00:43:06.630 --> 00:43:09.990 align:middle line:84%
Bingham called it the
Torreon, or Tower.

00:43:09.990 --> 00:43:12.480 align:middle line:84%
Today, it's known as
the Temple of the Sun.

00:43:12.480 --> 00:43:14.680 align:middle line:84%
It's built to a
semicircular plan,

00:43:14.680 --> 00:43:18.240 align:middle line:84%
with two trapezoidal windows
set in the curved wall.

00:43:18.240 --> 00:43:21.150 align:middle line:84%
One faces north, and
the other faces east.

00:43:21.150 --> 00:43:23.330 align:middle line:84%
They can be used to determine
the summer and winter

00:43:23.330 --> 00:43:24.130 align:middle line:90%
solstices.

00:43:24.130 --> 00:43:28.730 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:43:28.730 --> 00:43:31.600 align:middle line:90%


00:43:31.600 --> 00:43:34.300 align:middle line:84%
There is a niche with
structures carved into the lower

00:43:34.300 --> 00:43:36.280 align:middle line:90%
part of the building.

00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:41.230 align:middle line:84%
Its purpose was to determine
important astronomic events.

00:43:41.230 --> 00:43:44.080 align:middle line:84%
The Torreon is
more than a temple,

00:43:44.080 --> 00:43:46.150 align:middle line:84%
it's an astronomic
calendar in stone,

00:43:46.150 --> 00:43:48.760 align:middle line:84%
and it's not the only
one in Machu Picchu.

00:43:48.760 --> 00:43:50.380 align:middle line:84%
The Temple with
the Three Windows

00:43:50.380 --> 00:43:52.870 align:middle line:84%
is in the mid-level of the
city, and the alignment

00:43:52.870 --> 00:43:54.940 align:middle line:84%
of the openings
enables the equinoxes

00:43:54.940 --> 00:43:58.900 align:middle line:84%
to be calculated, the same
as the monolithic stones

00:43:58.900 --> 00:44:01.660 align:middle line:90%
of Stonehenge in England.

00:44:01.660 --> 00:44:06.770 align:middle line:10%
Stone is the great protagonist
of the ancient world.

00:44:06.770 --> 00:44:09.950 align:middle line:84%
But on a higher level, behind
a three-walled building reached

00:44:09.950 --> 00:44:11.870 align:middle line:84%
by a flight of
roughly hewn steps,

00:44:11.870 --> 00:44:13.760 align:middle line:84%
we find an even
more sophisticated

00:44:13.760 --> 00:44:15.013 align:middle line:90%
astronomic structure.

00:44:15.013 --> 00:44:19.090 align:middle line:90%


00:44:19.090 --> 00:44:21.690 align:middle line:84%
The Intihuatana is a
polygonal structure

00:44:21.690 --> 00:44:24.120 align:middle line:90%
cut into the living rock.

00:44:24.120 --> 00:44:26.630 align:middle line:90%
The precision is extraordinary.

00:44:26.630 --> 00:44:29.100 align:middle line:10%
A spur of rock like a
conch on the upper surface

00:44:29.100 --> 00:44:33.180 align:middle line:10%
is perfectly aligned to
the northeast, southeast,

00:44:33.180 --> 00:44:35.550 align:middle line:10%
an accurate sundial for
calculating the solstices

00:44:35.550 --> 00:44:37.860 align:middle line:10%
and the equinoxes.

00:44:37.860 --> 00:44:39.750 align:middle line:90%
Machu Picchu is incredible.

00:44:39.750 --> 00:44:41.550 align:middle line:84%
It's more like a
huge stone computer

00:44:41.550 --> 00:44:44.830 align:middle line:84%
for astronomical calculus,
rather than a city.

00:44:44.830 --> 00:44:47.340 align:middle line:10%
>> It's true that here at Machu
Picchu there are important

00:44:47.340 --> 00:44:50.850 align:middle line:10%
structures, both on the
lower and higher levels.

00:44:50.850 --> 00:44:54.030 align:middle line:10%
The actual position
of the city, it

00:44:54.030 --> 00:44:57.450 align:middle line:10%
was placed in the best position
to receive solar energy.

00:44:57.450 --> 00:44:59.700 align:middle line:84%
That's very clear
in Machu Picchu.

00:44:59.700 --> 00:45:02.160 align:middle line:84%
You can see both the
sunrise and the sunset.

00:45:02.160 --> 00:45:04.530 align:middle line:84%
It's positioned to receive
as much solar energy

00:45:04.530 --> 00:45:07.331 align:middle line:90%
as possible all year round.

00:45:07.331 --> 00:45:10.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Could the Inca empire have
developed such sophisticated

00:45:10.370 --> 00:45:12.720 align:middle line:90%
knowledge?

00:45:12.720 --> 00:45:14.870 align:middle line:84%
These are precise
technical instruments, not

00:45:14.870 --> 00:45:18.000 align:middle line:90%
simple ritual symbols.

00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:20.690 align:middle line:84%
They're backed up by precise,
geometrical calculations,

00:45:20.690 --> 00:45:23.040 align:middle line:90%
mathematics, and astronomy.

00:45:23.040 --> 00:45:24.620 align:middle line:84%
Only a civilization
that developed

00:45:24.620 --> 00:45:27.230 align:middle line:84%
over a long period of time
could have produced anything

00:45:27.230 --> 00:45:30.090 align:middle line:90%
like them.

00:45:30.090 --> 00:45:32.190 align:middle line:84%
Machu Picchu means
the old mountain.

00:45:32.190 --> 00:45:34.380 align:middle line:90%
But how old actually is it?

00:45:34.380 --> 00:45:36.390 align:middle line:84%
According to the
archaeologists, the city

00:45:36.390 --> 00:45:38.280 align:middle line:90%
was built in the 15th century.

00:45:38.280 --> 00:45:40.990 align:middle line:84%
But in 1930,
Professor Rolf Muller

00:45:40.990 --> 00:45:43.320 align:middle line:84%
from the University
of Potsdam in Germany

00:45:43.320 --> 00:45:46.170 align:middle line:84%
studied the astronomic
alignments of the Torreon,

00:45:46.170 --> 00:45:48.980 align:middle line:84%
the Temple with the Three
Windows, and the Intihuatana,

00:45:48.980 --> 00:45:51.330 align:middle line:84%
and established that they
had been built sometime

00:45:51.330 --> 00:45:53.860 align:middle line:90%
between 4,000 and 2000 BC.

00:45:53.860 --> 00:45:56.760 align:middle line:84%
These incredible dates were
confirmed by further studies,

00:45:56.760 --> 00:45:59.190 align:middle line:84%
carried out by the
astronomers Dearborn and White

00:45:59.190 --> 00:46:00.990 align:middle line:90%
from Arizona University.

00:46:00.990 --> 00:46:03.630 align:middle line:10%
Does this mean that
here, as in other sites,

00:46:03.630 --> 00:46:05.940 align:middle line:10%
the Incas settled on
preexisting structures?

00:46:05.940 --> 00:46:07.680 align:middle line:84%
The dates calculated
by the astronomers

00:46:07.680 --> 00:46:08.880 align:middle line:90%
confirm this theory.

00:46:08.880 --> 00:46:11.010 align:middle line:84%
Local oral traditions
that have been handed down

00:46:11.010 --> 00:46:13.530 align:middle line:84%
to the present day also
tell of ancient gods who

00:46:13.530 --> 00:46:16.830 align:middle line:84%
initiated civilization and
built wonderful cities, gods

00:46:16.830 --> 00:46:19.200 align:middle line:84%
who could fly, perhaps the
survivors of the highly

00:46:19.200 --> 00:46:21.870 align:middle line:90%
developed civilization of Mu.

00:46:21.870 --> 00:46:24.000 align:middle line:84%
On the sacred square
of Machu Picchu,

00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:26.490 align:middle line:84%
the Temple of the Three
Windows, the Main Temple,

00:46:26.490 --> 00:46:28.080 align:middle line:84%
and the other
structures, are all

00:46:28.080 --> 00:46:30.710 align:middle line:84%
built from perfectly fitted
together polygonal blocks.

00:46:30.710 --> 00:46:33.260 align:middle line:90%


00:46:33.260 --> 00:46:35.120 align:middle line:84%
The by now familiar
joints, already

00:46:35.120 --> 00:46:39.110 align:middle line:90%
seen in Cusco and Sacsayhuaman.

00:46:39.110 --> 00:46:44.150 align:middle line:84%
We find similar differences
in other parts of the city.

00:46:44.150 --> 00:46:45.950 align:middle line:84%
The difference in
style and technique

00:46:45.950 --> 00:46:50.660 align:middle line:84%
used to build Machu Picchu
are glaringly obvious.

00:46:50.660 --> 00:46:53.840 align:middle line:84%
Carefully crafted monoliths make
up the older part and rougher

00:46:53.840 --> 00:46:57.360 align:middle line:90%
workmanship on the later parts.

00:46:57.360 --> 00:46:59.940 align:middle line:84%
Once more, we find
different styles and levels

00:46:59.940 --> 00:47:01.740 align:middle line:90%
of technical ability.

00:47:01.740 --> 00:47:03.990 align:middle line:84%
Were they built by
different people?

00:47:03.990 --> 00:47:06.222 align:middle line:84%
How else can we
explain the difference?

00:47:06.222 --> 00:47:12.130 align:middle line:90%


00:47:12.130 --> 00:47:14.740 align:middle line:84%
But we have other
mysteries to unravel.

00:47:14.740 --> 00:47:17.110 align:middle line:84%
We want to know if there
were any underground tunnels

00:47:17.110 --> 00:47:18.659 align:middle line:90%
at Machu Picchu.

00:47:18.659 --> 00:47:20.950 align:middle line:10%
An we're told that when
maintenance work was being done

00:47:20.950 --> 00:47:24.190 align:middle line:10%
on the sacred square,
where the Main Temple is,

00:47:24.190 --> 00:47:29.470 align:middle line:10%
the workmen heard echoes as if
the ground below was hollow.

00:47:29.470 --> 00:47:32.810 align:middle line:84%
Some digging was done, but
only to a depth of a few feet,

00:47:32.810 --> 00:47:34.580 align:middle line:90%
without finding anything.

00:47:34.580 --> 00:47:39.050 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps the cavities
are further down.

00:47:39.050 --> 00:47:41.210 align:middle line:84%
A guide who heard
about our research

00:47:41.210 --> 00:47:44.240 align:middle line:84%
said that there was some
tunnels in another area.

00:47:44.240 --> 00:47:46.160 align:middle line:90%
He offers to take us there.

00:47:46.160 --> 00:47:49.460 align:middle line:84%
After a difficult scramble, we
come to the narrow entrance.

00:47:49.460 --> 00:47:54.860 align:middle line:90%


00:47:54.860 --> 00:47:59.300 align:middle line:84%
The young guide
climbs down first.

00:47:59.300 --> 00:48:00.450 align:middle line:90%
It's a tight squeeze.

00:48:00.450 --> 00:48:05.390 align:middle line:90%


00:48:05.390 --> 00:48:07.550 align:middle line:84%
Even passing the equipment,
we need to explore,

00:48:07.550 --> 00:48:13.920 align:middle line:84%
and film is difficult. We
can't really take all we need,

00:48:13.920 --> 00:48:15.485 align:middle line:90%
but we decide to make do.

00:48:15.485 --> 00:48:24.040 align:middle line:90%


00:48:24.040 --> 00:48:26.340 align:middle line:84%
Once we're in,
walking isn't easy.

00:48:26.340 --> 00:48:28.450 align:middle line:90%
The tunnel is very irregular.

00:48:28.450 --> 00:48:31.816 align:middle line:84%
It seems as if it had only
been started and not completed.

00:48:31.816 --> 00:48:37.650 align:middle line:90%


00:48:37.650 --> 00:48:40.539 align:middle line:84%
It's very damp, and the ground
underfoot is very slippery,

00:48:40.539 --> 00:48:41.580 align:middle line:90%
so we have to be careful.

00:48:41.580 --> 00:48:53.710 align:middle line:90%


00:48:53.710 --> 00:48:56.740 align:middle line:84%
After a certain distance,
the tunnel is blocked

00:48:56.740 --> 00:48:58.060 align:middle line:90%
and we can't go any further.

00:48:58.060 --> 00:49:04.470 align:middle line:90%


00:49:04.470 --> 00:49:06.810 align:middle line:84%
Getting back is
even more difficult,

00:49:06.810 --> 00:49:09.000 align:middle line:84%
but we have the
proof that someone

00:49:09.000 --> 00:49:12.241 align:middle line:84%
had created underground
tunnels at Machu Picchu, too.

00:49:12.241 --> 00:49:18.820 align:middle line:90%


00:49:18.820 --> 00:49:22.090 align:middle line:84%
The sun is setting as we
emerge from the narrow tunnel.

00:49:22.090 --> 00:49:24.670 align:middle line:84%
The ancient city is
hauntingly beautiful

00:49:24.670 --> 00:49:26.530 align:middle line:84%
and had shared some of
its secrets with us.

00:49:26.530 --> 00:49:29.200 align:middle line:90%


00:49:29.200 --> 00:49:32.560 align:middle line:84%
Our minds are echoing with
the words of Colonel Fawcett,

00:49:32.560 --> 00:49:34.870 align:middle line:84%
"The Indios tribes
inherited the traditions

00:49:34.870 --> 00:49:36.670 align:middle line:90%
of a great civilization.

00:49:36.670 --> 00:49:39.820 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps they were the
ancestors of the Incas,

00:49:39.820 --> 00:49:43.300 align:middle line:84%
perhaps a mysterious race
who left behind the gigantic

00:49:43.300 --> 00:49:46.300 align:middle line:84%
remains that the invading
Incas later incorporated

00:49:46.300 --> 00:49:48.214 align:middle line:90%
into their own buildings."

00:49:48.214 --> 00:49:52.170 align:middle line:90%


00:49:52.170 --> 00:49:55.740 align:middle line:84%
Historical civilizations all
have a common matrix, albeit a

00:49:55.740 --> 00:49:56.730 align:middle line:90%
forgotten one.

00:49:56.730 --> 00:50:00.150 align:middle line:84%
Even Colonel Fawcett was
convinced of the truth of this.

00:50:00.150 --> 00:50:03.440 align:middle line:84%
The huge ruins scattered
around Peru and other countries

00:50:03.440 --> 00:50:05.660 align:middle line:84%
around the world
are an obvious clue,

00:50:05.660 --> 00:50:10.000 align:middle line:84%
confirmed by their identical
construction technique.

00:50:10.000 --> 00:50:12.240 align:middle line:84%
The myths and traditions
of many ancient people

00:50:12.240 --> 00:50:16.250 align:middle line:84%
have handed down the memory
of this civilization.

00:50:16.250 --> 00:50:18.435 align:middle line:84%
There are mysterious tunnels
at these ancient sites.

00:50:18.435 --> 00:50:21.960 align:middle line:90%


00:50:21.960 --> 00:50:23.550 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps these
clues are still not

00:50:23.550 --> 00:50:26.760 align:middle line:84%
enough to prove the existence
of a lost civilization which

00:50:26.760 --> 00:50:31.410 align:middle line:84%
gave rise to all
successive civilizations.

00:50:31.410 --> 00:50:34.240 align:middle line:84%
There is still a
lot to discover,

00:50:34.240 --> 00:50:37.920 align:middle line:90%
and the research goes on.

